00:00:00.000 --> 00:00:01.740
MATT: OK, so I'm going to
do a card trick based

00:00:01.740 --> 00:00:03.430
on the number 27.

00:00:03.430 --> 00:00:06.180
And this is my all-time favorite
maths card trick.

00:00:06.180 --> 00:00:08.750
And I'm going to show it for
you today, and I'm going to

00:00:08.750 --> 00:00:10.460
explain it.

00:00:10.460 --> 00:00:15.040
I found this trick in an old
1950's math book written by

00:00:15.040 --> 00:00:16.170
Martin Gardner.

00:00:16.170 --> 00:00:19.530
And for me it is the maths
card trick with the most

00:00:19.530 --> 00:00:21.590
beautiful maths behind it
out of all of them.

00:00:21.590 --> 00:00:24.946
And because it is a math card
trick, it does involve a lot

00:00:24.946 --> 00:00:26.570
of long tedious counting.

00:00:26.570 --> 00:00:27.510
But bear with us here.

00:00:27.510 --> 00:00:31.500
So this involves 27 cards, so
I'm going to take 27 off.

00:00:31.500 --> 00:00:32.880
And this is a genuine count.

00:00:32.880 --> 00:00:36.550
One, two, three, four, five,
six, seven, eight, nine, 10.

00:00:36.550 --> 00:00:38.530
27 is actually one of my
favorite numbers--

00:00:38.530 --> 00:00:42.720
One, two, three, four, five,
six, seven, eight, nine, 10--

00:00:42.720 --> 00:00:43.670
because it's a cubed number.

00:00:43.670 --> 00:00:47.110
One, two, three, four,
five, six, seven.

00:00:47.110 --> 00:00:47.730
OK, that's 27 cards.

00:00:47.730 --> 00:00:50.530
And this works with any 27
cards, and none of this trick

00:00:50.530 --> 00:00:51.850
is slight-of-hand.

00:00:51.850 --> 00:00:55.900
None of it is YouTube magic
where I'm using something

00:00:55.900 --> 00:00:57.890
sneaky, or a sneaky edit.

00:00:57.890 --> 00:00:59.770
And I'll explain the trick
afterwards, so it's OK.

00:00:59.770 --> 00:01:00.520
But this is how works--

00:01:00.520 --> 00:01:02.160
You get 27 cards, you
shuffle them up.

00:01:02.160 --> 00:01:04.569
I'm actually going to
get Brady to both

00:01:04.569 --> 00:01:05.980
film and be the volunteer.

00:01:05.980 --> 00:01:08.580
So I'll flick through, do you
want to tap which one you

00:01:08.580 --> 00:01:09.940
want, which one of these?

00:01:09.940 --> 00:01:10.390
OK that one there.

00:01:10.390 --> 00:01:11.960
Do you want to show you
the camera that card?

00:01:11.960 --> 00:01:13.225
Don't let me see
it, obviously.

00:01:13.225 --> 00:01:16.290
And do you want to put it back
in wherever you want?

00:01:16.290 --> 00:01:16.322
Thank you.

00:01:16.322 --> 00:01:18.870
Now all he needs to do is just
remember what that card was,

00:01:18.870 --> 00:01:20.450
and believe me, people in the
comments will mention

00:01:20.450 --> 00:01:21.460
afterwards if you don't.

00:01:21.460 --> 00:01:23.950
Brady what's your favorite
number from 1 to 27, if you

00:01:23.950 --> 00:01:25.800
had to pick a number?

00:01:25.800 --> 00:01:26.710
BRADY: 10.

00:01:26.710 --> 00:01:28.110
MATT: 10, any particular
reason why 10?

00:01:28.110 --> 00:01:29.556
BRADY: I just like
